3. Research, Technology, and the Presentation of Information
​Scenario 1: Parsing Flat-File Seed Data into Structured Relational SQL Tables
​A core requirement of the project assignment was the ability to drop existing database tables and dynamically rebuild them using data extracted from external text files (userData.txt and clothingData.txt). To achieve this, I had to conduct deep research into native PHP file-system functions and string manipulation techniques.
​I investigated the mechanics of the file() and file_get_contents() functions, analyzing how to safely open, read line-by-line, and isolate raw data strings. I researched how to apply functions like explode() to break down tab-delimited or space-separated plain text profiles, stripping out trailing white spaces using trim().
​This research was vital to ensure that when includes/createTable.php ran, it could programmatically loop through the unstructured text rows, isolate fields like names and emails, hash default passwords securely, and execute safe database insertions. Presenting this clean automation ensured our submission met the strict structural requirements outlined in the PoE checklist.
​Scenario 2: Managing Background Network Requests via Asynchronous JavaScript
​Another critical research scenario involved creating a modern, reactive user interface that bypassed traditional synchronous form submittals. I was tasked with investigating how to transmit data silently in the background when a user clicked "Add to Wishlist."
​I conducted thorough research into modern Asynchronous JavaScript and XML (AJAX) using the native Web fetch() API. I analyzed how to properly structure HTTP POST requests, pass request parameters safely within headers, and handle returned JSON response codes asynchronously using JavaScript Promises (.then() and .catch()). On the server backend, I researched how to structure ajax/wishlist.php to intercept these background payloads, process active user login sessions, modify tblWishlist entries, and return an explicit status code back to the client. This research allowed us to build a fluid, high-fidelity browsing experience where items glow or transition state instantly upon click, elevating the presentation quality of the platform.
